Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.80,0:00:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you refuse my call to be subjugated?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.09,0:00:14.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never swear allegiance to\Nthe man who killed Lord Villar!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:26.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Glory to... Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This castle and throne\Nshall be relinquished to you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.28,0:00:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it does not mean Altirk has been defeated.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.33,0:00:40.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.33,0:00:44.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I rule here, this is no longer Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.21,0:00:46.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's Dartania now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:50.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!\NThe scum who murdered Lord Villar!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:55.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-Lord Villar...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:00:57.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Villar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.43,0:01:01.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You accomplished nothing in life...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.56,0:01:07.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you hope to do in death?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.55,0:02:59.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, during the last battle,\NLord Villar lost his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:04.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the rest of us\Ncannot afford to wallow in grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.76,0:03:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Waldlind, Dartania and Nord\Nwill surely proceed with their invasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.69,0:03:13.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To rise against them,\Nit is imperative that we stand together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.65,0:03:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Many of you Lords have gathered here to\Ncarry on the legacy of Lord Villar, Earl of Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.66,0:03:27.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As ratified by you all, I hereby proclaim\Nthe establishment of the Altirk Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:38.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.72,0:03:41.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who will be our leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.81,0:03:52.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Lord Villar's own younger brother,\NLord Selge, is the natural choice, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:03:56.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I want to avenge my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:03:59.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I am not worthy for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.61,0:04:00.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.99,0:04:03.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because he wishes to reclaim his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.49,0:04:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Selge believes Earl Lassic David\Nshould lead us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.96,0:04:13.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Lord Lassic, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:16.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's the right man for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.59,0:04:17.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.76,0:04:22.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, but I cannot be your leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:28.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reason being that I'm only holding\Nmy court rank for Sir Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.56,0:04:34.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you did serve as\NSir Theo's subjugated Lord originally.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.65,0:04:37.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, and I plan to\Nserve him again one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In my mind, no one would make a better leader\Nthan Sir Theo. What do you all think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I oppose such an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.20,0:04:56.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo once repelled Waldlind,\Nmaking him a sworn enemy in their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:59.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he becomes our leader, they're sure to\Nlaunch an all-out assault on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:03.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless who our leader is,\Nthe Alliance certainly won't show us mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.97,0:05:06.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the Union will have its hands tied.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:12.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which is precisely why our leader\Nmust be someone you can all agree on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.60,0:05:16.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that person is not Sir Theo,\Nbut Lord Lassic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:20.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored that so many of you have such\Nhigh expectations of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.23,0:05:24.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this is between Sir Theo and I–
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:26.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm grateful for your loyalty, Lassic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:31.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But all the Lords here\Nwant you to be our leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:37.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They don't find me qualified to be your master.\NThat's what it comes down to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.67,0:05:38.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.42,0:05:44.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who you choose to lead us is your decision.\NBut I do have my pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:48.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to prove that I'm a Lord worthy of\NLord Lassic's loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.14,0:05:50.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.97,0:05:55.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will make my mark in the upcoming war,\Nso you will have to acknowledge me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:59.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just how convincing a performance\Ndo you plan on making?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.19,0:06:02.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As this is a matter\Nbetween master and subject...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.28,0:06:07.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see why we shouldn't\Nleave it up to Lord Lassic and Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:11.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While the rest of us\Ncan serve as their witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.54,0:06:13.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's elect Lord Lassic as our leader,\Nand decide later when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.08,0:06:19.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you all agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:20.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.84,0:06:21.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.42,0:06:27.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Invade Regalia, she says?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.55,0:06:32.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine says she'll leave\Nthe post-invasion matters to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:37.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may either subjugate Regalia,\Nor withdraw without conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.73,0:06:38.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.23,0:06:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine intends to reclaim Bultava, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.94,0:06:45.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we're to pose a threat from the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:48.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe your instincts are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.36,0:06:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll leave five hundred men or so\Nto defend the castle, and mobilize in full force.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.62,0:06:57.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Starting with Regalia, if we conquer all\Nterritories previously under Villar's command,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:07:00.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the Altirk Lords will have\Nno choice but to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.83,0:07:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly hope it ends up that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:04.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You believe it won't?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regalia and the other nations signed a pact,\Nlead by Lassic, the King of Sievis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.10,0:07:13.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm told they're ready to rise up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:17.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who our opponents may be,\Nthey have no prayer against Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.89,0:07:22.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While we should be wary of Lassic,\Neven he can't appear on every battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.31,0:07:29.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but this time, I believe it's crucial for us\Nto recognize our foe's abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you giving me your opinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:34.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're only Lady Marrine's\Ncontracted mage, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:37.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm here because\Nshe sent me to serve you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.33,0:07:42.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then from here on,\Nbe bolder with your recommendations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:49.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And be fully prepared to\Nget slashed if you anger me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:51.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.61,0:08:12.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose we must concede that\NPrince Milza is a brilliant leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.70,0:08:16.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have the men fall back\Nto their designated positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.24,0:08:20.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, you shall go in as our decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:21.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:35.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:38.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Head for Selge Constance in full force!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lassic David!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.53,0:09:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As expected, I was no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.54,0:09:06.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, you didn't lose many men, and it was\Na brilliant call you made against Milza.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:07.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave the rest to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:14.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:56.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Lassic!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.56,0:10:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like my head's still intact somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.48,0:10:08.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milza Kuches...\NSuch a terrifying man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:15.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lassic David...\NI knew you were no ordinary man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.57,0:10:21.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are those Igor Constance's troops?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:24.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The odds would be against us\Nif we engaged them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.71,0:10:29.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough!\NHead back to our homeland!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.88,0:10:38.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I let my chance to kill Lassic slip away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.60,0:10:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The master of the castle is Theo Cornaro,\Nwith about three thousand troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:49.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three thousand?\NMore than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.06,0:10:53.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think he'd muster that many men\Nin such a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:58.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you get the feeling\Nwe should've allied with him that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.45,0:11:01.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is for you to determine, Lady Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.\NAnd it's not as if I regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.91,0:11:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, it's that I don't wish to go to war
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.50,0:11:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,against him and his\Ncontracted mage, Siluca Meletes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.50,0:11:19.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Altirk Teaty drawn up by him and his allies\Nis a declaration of war against the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:23.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no question that\Nhe is a Lord whom we must vanquish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.06,0:11:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But before heading into battle,\NI'd like to meet with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.98,0:11:34.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then shall I arrange a summit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.49,0:11:42.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A summit, huh?\NWhat is there to discuss now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:44.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's futile to negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not only does Waldlind\Nintend to reclaim this land,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.58,0:11:49.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no way we can withdraw, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:55.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm sure Father is aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.71,0:11:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, Lady Marrine wishes\Nto meet with you, Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.22,0:12:00.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.68,0:12:03.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Waldlind's forces are superior to ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:07.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt even Father has\Nany dark schemes in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.72,0:12:12.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, Lady Marrine simply\Nhas an interest in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.40,0:12:13.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.06,0:12:17.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then I'll meet with her.\NI wish to tell her something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:22.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although your father's\Nprobably going to be there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.95,0:12:26.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and I was sure that I was\Nnever going to see Father again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you do want to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.33,0:12:32.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought you were\Nafraid of your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I admit that, as a mage,\NFather is a cold, heartless man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.17,0:12:45.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a student at the Mage Academy,\Nhe even tried to kill me once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.76,0:12:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kill you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.97,0:12:53.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was for breaking the rules and almost\Ngetting expelled. It couldn't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:57.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father was only following\Nthe bylaws of the Mage Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.82,0:12:59.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's still no reason to take your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.98,0:13:04.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Despite it all, he's still my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.99,0:13:08.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.79,0:13:16.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. The summit hasn't started yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.03,0:13:43.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.90,0:13:46.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite young. The rumors were true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.28,0:13:52.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike all the rumors,\Nyou seem very gentle, Margrave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.29,0:13:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those close to me\Nhave been known to say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.08,0:13:59.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.05,0:14:01.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.30,0:14:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was kind enough to call me his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:06.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.68,0:14:10.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis still loves you\Nwith all his heart, even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I'd very much like it\Nif you two could be united.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:19.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd expect no less from\Na friend of the Marquis of Jalucia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:21.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you, too, are a dreamer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I was told the same thing\Nby the Earl of Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.20,0:14:26.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By Lord Villar?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.57,0:14:30.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those were... his last words.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.53,0:14:32.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's so–
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:36.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were too naive.\NBoth myself and Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.58,0:14:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We never even realized there those\Nwho didn't want the era of Chaos to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.51,0:14:48.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I've resolved to\Nunite the continent by military force.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.97,0:14:54.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this great war continues,\Nthen our Crests will eventually be fused.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:58.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should that happen, it won't be long before\Nthose who writhe in the darkness emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.69,0:15:03.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to wipe them out,\Nand bring about an era where Lords rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:05.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I myself am a Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Doing so will cause much bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.86,0:15:10.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepared for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:19.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to strive for the same ideals\Nwhich you've abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:21.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you up to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.29,0:15:26.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because Siluca will show me the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:27.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.26,0:15:33.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you gave up your\Ncourt rank and territories for Lady Siluca.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.93,0:15:37.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply considered what was precious to me\Nbefore making my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.48,0:15:38.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:43.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Though in my case, what turned out to be\Nmore precious was not Alexis,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but Waldlind, and the Factory Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:50.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.61,0:15:55.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wish fight you, Lord Theo,\Nbut I must reclaim this territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:16:00.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wish to fight you, either,\Nbut there's no way I'm giving in to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.04,0:16:03.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.63,0:16:07.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let us meet again on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt that Lady Marrine\Nis in love with Lord Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:20.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to find a way to bring them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:24.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But to make that happen,\Nyou're going to need a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.19,0:16:27.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then could you work a miracle for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.57,0:16:30.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Easier said than done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}This time, the Alliance and Union will reconcile,\Nand Lady Marrine and Lord Alexis will be united!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.87,0:16:42.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's turn the Great Hall Tragedy into a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.10,0:17:01.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo!\NThis is neither the time nor place to–
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.39,0:17:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.36,0:17:07.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of your love!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.90,0:17:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of your love!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.57,0:17:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of your love!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:25.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, did you just provoke Lady Marrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:29.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just want her to remember\Nwhat it is that's precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.63,0:17:33.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This battle won't be easy to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:37.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll be trying to achieve something\Nno one on the continent has thought about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.93,0:17:41.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't afford to die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.35,0:17:44.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so embarrassed,\NI might die right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Love won't help me defend this castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.61,0:17:56.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nor my people or country!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.28,0:17:59.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine, I have a report for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:04.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Waldlind forces are retreating?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.12,0:18:07.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Earl of Le Couleurs, Croute Gallas,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.75,0:18:12.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,has crushed the Alliance forces led by\NNord King Erik in the battle up north,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.34,0:18:14.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and is still giving chase as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:20.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This will leave Waldlind vulnerable from behind,\Nso it's probably why they're retreating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:23.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, this is the perfect opportunity!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:29.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Waldlind's withdrawn,\Nthe main battlefield will likely shift to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.77,0:18:32.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now is the time to head to Sistina.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:38.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you were going to turn\Nthe Great Hall Tragedy into a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That you wanted them to be able to marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.41,0:18:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to make that a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:48.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you must achieve a rank equal to that\Nof Lord Alexis and Lady Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.08,0:18:53.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you must become\Nthe leader of the Altirk Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:59.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To that end, you must defeat the Rossini family,\Nand liberate Sistina from oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.05,0:19:03.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now is the time for you to\Nfulfill your original vow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.47,0:19:08.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use those military achievements to\Nget the Treaty Lords to recognize your power!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:14.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I shall show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.24,0:19:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How ridiculous is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:24.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Rossini's have hordes of loyal,\Nsubjugated Lords and soldiers at their disposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.12,0:19:27.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need at least 10,000 men to attack them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.87,0:19:32.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With the fight against the Alliance still ongoing,\Nno one can spare any troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.13,0:19:36.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to flaunt Sir Theo's power\Nthrough military manpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.21,0:19:41.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we won't ask for aid from the other Lords.\NIt'll be just us heading to Sistina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.10,0:19:43.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.47,0:19:44.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.44,0:19:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way, the Treaty Lords will have no choice\Nbut to acknowledge your achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.02,0:19:56.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And nobody will object to\Nmy relinquishing leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.28,0:20:00.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moreno, notify the Lords right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.53,0:20:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To make good on what he said at the meeting,\NSir Theo has set off to liberate Sistina!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:06.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.41,0:20:10.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave this place to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.37,0:20:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Return to your homeland and fulfill your vow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.34,0:20:15.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:23.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A TREATY FORMED
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.16,0:22:08.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.78,0:22:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:12.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro is on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.75,0:22:13.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say Cornaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.37,0:22:18.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a descendant.\NHe's only calling himself that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.67,0:22:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, the Lord you said you saw at\Nthe Union congress?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.55,0:22:26.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he said he'd be coming\Nto this island one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.60,0:22:34.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what he could be planning to do\Non this island ruled by us Rossinis?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.81,0:22:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But on this island, Cornaro is known\Nas the name of a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.90,0:22:43.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone coming here, assuming that name...\NI don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.57,0:22:45.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Juzel's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.15,0:22:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Theo Cornaro is not to be taken lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.28,0:22:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even the smallest spark\Ncan set off a raging fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.91,0:22:58.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we need to exercise extreme caution,\Nand eliminate him with all our power.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.01,0:23:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're short on taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.13,0:23:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The effects of the Chaos reduced my yield, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.34,0:23:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's more in that\Nstorehouse over there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.01,0:23:15.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's for us to eat, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.48,0:23:16.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.73,0:23:20.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, have a heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.23,0:23:22.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you take any more from us,\Nwe'll starve to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.90,0:23:24.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.45,0:23:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, sir! I beg of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 13:\NTO THE HOMELAND
